** The Integration Engineer will work together with teams across to:   
**   
• design, implement, and maintain seamless integration solutions within our
technology ecosystem  
• be responsible for collaborating with cross-functional teams, leveraging
technical expertise in C#, microservices, and Azure to enhance system
connectivity and optimize data flow  
• be passionate about integration technologies, enjoy problem-solving, and
have a strong desire to learn and grow in a collaborative environment  
  
** Experience - Mandatory **   
• ** C#: Proficiency in C# programming language for developing robust and
efficient integration solutions. **  
• Microservices Knowledge: Understanding and practical experience with
microservices architecture.  
• ** Azure Experience: Hands-on experience with Azure services, including but
not limited to Azure Logic Apps, Azure Service Bus, and Azure Functions. **  
• Critical Thinking: Strong analytical and problem-solving skills to address
complex integration challenges.  
• ** Debugging with Azure: Ability to effectively debug and troubleshoot
integration issues using Azure tools and resources. **  
• Strong Team engagement, ability to influence and lead the change journey  
**   
Experience – Nice to have **  
• Azure Functions: Familiarity with serverless computing and the ability to
leverage Azure Functions in integration scenarios.  
• API Management: Knowledge of Azure API Management to create, publish, and
manage APIs effectively.  
• Domain Driven Design (DDD): Understanding of DDD principles and their
application in designing integrations aligned with business domains.  
• Infrastructure as Code (IaC): Experience with IaC tools such as Terraform or
Azure Resource Manager templates  
  
